      <hedline>
        <hl1>Vieques Island</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>William B Horn letter on Claudia Dreifus' April 9 travel article disputes her take on fare and service at Cafe Blu</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor: Claudia Dreifus writes that at Cafe Blu she encountered snootery. My experiences on four evenings in January and February were just the opposite.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor: Claudia Dreifus writes that at Cafe Blu she encountered snootery. My experiences on four evenings in January and February were just the opposite.</p>
        <p>As for the pacing of seating times to accommodate the ability of  the small kitchen to deliver excellent food, that is common enough  and certainly better than people waiting unhappily at their tables.</p>
        <p>WILLIAM B. HORN  Minneapolis</p>
      </block>
